01:08:02,749 --> 01:08:06,284
Ain't gonna be enough hide on you
to patch a pinole.

734
01:08:06,461 --> 01:08:08,205
Just counselling the chief.

735
01:08:08,422 --> 01:08:14,211
I'm a little more civilized than him,
and I want to get my two cents in.

736
01:08:14,428 --> 01:08:17,429
Give me trouble, I'll kill you,
understand?

737
01:08:17,639 --> 01:08:20,047
- Yes.
- Say it. Convince me.

738
01:08:20,267 --> 01:08:23,802
- Any more trouble, you'll kill me.
- I believe you.

739
01:08:24,021 --> 01:08:28,184
So from now on,
whether you live or die is up to you.

740
01:08:28,442 --> 01:08:32,142
Excuse me.
Can I go to the bathroom?

741
01:08:34,698 --> 01:08:37,154
We gotta get something straight.

742
01:08:37,367 --> 01:08:41,365
I threatened to drag him
and you threatened to kill him.

743
01:08:41,622 --> 01:08:45,489
- I don't like being out-threatened.
- Wort happen again.

744
01:08:45,709 --> 01:08:48,544
Bad as being upstaged.
I'm a movie star.

745
01:08:52,508 --> 01:08:53,836
Why are you here?

746
01:08:54,051 --> 01:08:56,624
You don't come here.
We had an agreement.

747
01:08:56,845 --> 01:08:58,221
Had an agreement.

748
01:08:58,430 --> 01:09:00,589
What's that supposed to mean?

749
01:09:00,807 --> 01:09:04,342
Any agreement didn't include
you beating Victoria.

750
01:09:04,561 --> 01:09:06,139
What? What do you...?

751
01:09:06,355 --> 01:09:08,976
- Did Victoria tell you that?
- She did.

752
01:09:09,233 --> 01:09:12,815
She fingered Mix,
but I know what really happened.

753
01:09:13,070 --> 01:09:15,442
And how do you know?

754
01:09:15,656 --> 01:09:17,529
A year ago we made a deal.

755
01:09:17,783 --> 01:09:21,781
I don't deal with anyone
I don't know everything about.

756
01:09:21,995 --> 01:09:24,035
I know who and what you are.

757
01:09:24,248 --> 01:09:28,376
I knew a guy like you
when I was starting. Cocky guy.

758
01:09:28,585 --> 01:09:30,459
Wore spats and a derby.

759
01:09:30,963 --> 01:09:33,714
He used to brag about how smart he was.

760
01:09:33,966 --> 01:09:37,216
Till someone shot him in the mouth.

761
01:09:37,886 --> 01:09:40,971
If Mix is arrested,
what happens to his movie?

762
01:09:41,473 --> 01:09:45,601
I'll close down for a few days.
We'll recast.

763
01:09:45,811 --> 01:09:48,053
Tom Mix will be washed up.

764
01:09:48,355 --> 01:09:51,273
Provided he's found guilty.

765
01:09:51,483 --> 01:09:53,725
The press will find him guilty.

766
01:09:53,986 --> 01:09:57,070
Blackwon'th's arresting Mix is okay.

767
01:09:57,322 --> 01:10:00,738
But not until I get
Candy's little black book.

768
01:10:00,951 --> 01:10:03,620
- How will you do that?
- Nancy Shoemaker.

769
01:10:03,829 --> 01:10:06,498
Mix is hiding her up at his ranch.

770
01:10:08,250 --> 01:10:13,126
A woman called, but wouldn't
leave her name. She sounded disturbed.

771
01:10:13,380 --> 01:10:16,879
- You didn't recognize the voice?
- It was English.

772
01:10:17,092 --> 01:10:20,591
She asked if you could be reached.

773
01:10:20,804 --> 01:10:22,880
I'll get it.

774
01:10:23,390 --> 01:10:24,421
Hello.

775
01:10:24,641 --> 01:10:26,433
- Tom.
- Yes?

776
01:10:26,643 --> 01:10:29,134
This is Christina.

777
01:10:30,022 --> 01:10:33,806
Dutch Kieffer knows you've got Nancy
up at the ranch...

778
01:10:41,783 --> 01:10:44,488
Strap on your iron, we're saving Nancy.

779
01:11:00,761 --> 01:11:02,919
This here is my flying buddy!

780
01:11:03,138 --> 01:11:04,882
- Wyatt, Cheryl!
- Hi!

781
01:11:05,140 --> 01:11:07,133
What about the funeral?

782
01:11:07,392 --> 01:11:10,678
If you're not back,
take Cheryl to the funeral!

783
01:11:10,938 --> 01:11:13,773
Come on, Wyatt! We gotta go!

784
01:11:20,155 --> 01:11:22,314
- You ever done any flying?
- Nope!

785
01:11:22,533 --> 01:11:24,193
Me neither!

786
01:11:24,451 --> 01:11:27,785
- It's still dark!
- It'll be dawn in 10 minutes!

787
01:11:28,038 --> 01:11:30,659
Fasten your seat belt!

788
01:12:40,068 --> 01:12:42,394
How much further?

789
01:12:42,779 --> 01:12:44,190
About 50 miles.

790
01:13:10,432 --> 01:13:12,425
Oh, shit!

791
01:13:37,709 --> 01:13:39,951
What do you think you're doing?

792
01:13:40,170 --> 01:13:42,875
Mostly trying to stay alive.

793
01:13:43,507 --> 01:13:45,298
Hey, I know you.

794
01:13:45,509 --> 01:13:47,300
- Ain't you...?
- Yeah.

795
01:13:47,553 --> 01:13:49,047
That's Tom Mix.

796
01:13:49,304 --> 01:13:52,590
Wyatt, I want you to meet...
What are your names?

797
01:13:52,808 --> 01:13:55,299
- This is Henry.
- And this is Fred.

798
01:13:55,519 --> 01:13:58,140
I want you to meet Wyatt Earp.

799
01:13:58,397 --> 01:14:00,685
- Wyatt?
- Earp?

800
01:14:00,899 --> 01:14:02,607
Morning, boys.

801
01:14:02,860 --> 01:14:05,896
- Where are we?
- Now you're on the Circle C.

802
01:14:06,113 --> 01:14:08,948
About 15 miles southeast
of your spread.

803
01:14:09,157 --> 01:14:13,535
We sure would appreciate the loan
of a couple fast horses.

804
01:14:57,122 --> 01:15:01,072
I'm getting to where I can't
even stay on a horse.

805
01:15:01,919 --> 01:15:03,995
Go on!

806
01:15:27,736 --> 01:15:30,108
Hey, what do you want?

807
01:15:30,364 --> 01:15:32,107
What do you want?

808
01:16:11,822 --> 01:16:16,567
Let go of me, you big bastard!

809
01:16:25,878 --> 01:16:29,827
- You'll be all right?
- I'd feel better if they was a camera.

810
01:16:30,090 --> 01:16:32,415
Let's get her done.

811
01:16:34,428 --> 01:16:36,219
Get in the car!

812
01:16:36,471 --> 01:16:39,093
Get in there and shut up!

813
01:16:40,058 --> 01:16:42,431
Spread out!

814
01:17:06,293 --> 01:17:08,914
Get off me!

815
01:17:21,683 --> 01:17:23,343
My God!

816
01:17:23,560 --> 01:17:24,971
Wyatt.

817
01:17:25,187 --> 01:17:27,559
Well, you done good, pardner.

818
01:17:27,773 --> 01:17:31,640
Of course, a couple more inches...

819
01:17:38,742 --> 01:17:41,826
To assure the resurrection
to eternal life...

820
01:17:42,037 --> 01:17:44,326
...through the Lord, Jesus Christ...

821
01:17:44,540 --> 01:17:48,584
...we commend thee, Almighty God,
our sister, Candace Girard.

822
01:17:48,836 --> 01:17:50,875
We commit her to the ground.

823
01:17:51,088 --> 01:17:55,833
Earth to earth, ashes to ashes,
dust to dust.

824
01:17:56,093 --> 01:17:58,465
- Amen.
- Amen.

825
01:18:01,014 --> 01:18:03,766
Bless you, my child.

826
01:18:05,894 --> 01:18:08,219
Cheryl King?

827
01:18:08,480 --> 01:18:09,511
Yes.

828
01:18:09,773 --> 01:18:13,818
I would've given you this sooner,
but I couldn't find you.

829
01:18:14,069 --> 01:18:15,647
My card.

830
01:18:15,863 --> 01:18:20,026
If you need help, please call.

831
01:18:30,294 --> 01:18:32,333
I'm sorry.

832
01:18:36,133 --> 01:18:40,047
- A man gave me this envelope.
- Open it.

833
01:18:40,929 --> 01:18:43,930
You know a Leo Vogel, attorney?

834
01:18:44,183 --> 01:18:45,558
No.

835
01:18:47,394 --> 01:18:49,600
It's a safety deposit box key.

836
01:18:49,813 --> 01:18:52,387
I'm glad you boys finally showed up.

837
01:18:52,649 --> 01:18:55,271
What are you doing here, Blackwon'th?

838
01:18:55,485 --> 01:18:59,020
I'm about to arrest America's
favourite star cowboy...

839
01:18:59,239 --> 01:19:01,564
...for felonious assault and rape.

840
01:19:01,783 --> 01:19:03,859
Unless you try to stop me.

841
01:19:04,119 --> 01:19:06,325
And I hope you do.

842
01:19:06,538 --> 01:19:07,617
Rape?

843
01:19:07,873 --> 01:19:10,115
You're kidding. Who did I rape?

844
01:19:10,667 --> 01:19:13,752
You'll find out about
that at the station.

845
01:19:14,004 --> 01:19:16,127
Let's go.

846
01:19:16,340 --> 01:19:17,585
I'm primed.

847
01:19:17,799 --> 01:19:19,709
You wanna take him?

848
01:19:19,927 --> 01:19:23,545
I'd like to, but he's not won'th it.

849
01:19:26,934 --> 01:19:29,685
You bit off more than you can chew.

850
01:19:29,895 --> 01:19:32,600
Call my lawyer, Saul Rosenstein.

851
01:19:32,856 --> 01:19:35,727
I'll be all right, honey.
You go with them.

852
01:19:38,529 --> 01:19:42,443
I'd run you and your
lesbo girlfriend out of town...

853
01:19:42,699 --> 01:19:45,819
...but you made some
dangerous enemies here.

854
01:19:46,036 --> 01:19:50,532
I'm looking forward to what's
gonna happen when they catch you.

855
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:54,289
How's your nose?

856
01:19:55,504 --> 01:19:58,873
Get out of here,
before I forget I'm a lawman.

857
01:19:59,091 --> 01:20:02,092
I don't think you
killed half those men.

858
01:20:02,302 --> 01:20:07,213
And the ones you did kill,
I bet you shot them in the back.

859
01:20:09,977 --> 01:20:13,511
Let's find out, you son of a bitch.
Draw.

860
01:20:20,737 --> 01:20:22,896
My men will cut you to ribbons.

861
01:20:23,365 --> 01:20:27,030
Not before I shoot out your eyes.

862
01:20:35,252 --> 01:20:37,660
Another time.

863
01:20:50,350 --> 01:20:52,509
- Would you have killed him?
- No.

864
01:20:52,728 --> 01:20:53,759
Why?

865
01:20:53,979 --> 01:20:56,648
I'm not packing a gun.

866
01:21:02,487 --> 01:21:06,865
- Hey, ain't you Tom Mix?
- I sure am, pardner.

867
01:21:08,076 --> 01:21:11,196
Tom, you need a new sidekick?

868
01:21:19,087 --> 01:21:22,955
- Can I get you anything?
- I don't expect to be here long.

869
01:21:23,133 --> 01:21:25,541
Don't count on it.

870
01:21:26,887 --> 01:21:30,837
- Hello, Michael. How are you, boy?
- Not very well.

871
01:21:31,016 --> 01:21:34,100
- Mind if I ask you a question?
- Yes, I was framed.

872
01:21:34,478 --> 01:21:35,937
Who'd do that?

873
01:21:36,104 --> 01:21:40,434
Whoever got the bartender to drug me,
then had me go to Candy's.

874
01:21:40,651 --> 01:21:43,770
- And you found her dead.
- No.

875
01:21:44,571 --> 01:21:48,023
She said, "Never trust an Alperin,"
then she died.

876
01:21:48,367 --> 01:21:54,737
She was trying to name the killer. She
just didn't have time to be specific.

877
01:21:54,915 --> 01:21:59,292
You can take your pick, though.
I mean, there are four Alperins.

878
01:21:59,461 --> 01:22:04,088
Well, three, if my mother
decides to narrow the field.

879
01:22:04,341 --> 01:22:06,084
What do you mean?

880
01:22:06,260 --> 01:22:07,920
You didn't hear?

881
01:22:09,388 --> 01:22:13,220
She's in the hospital.
She's not expected to live.

882
01:22:41,962 --> 01:22:44,797
How much do you think there is?

883
01:22:44,965 --> 01:22:47,041
Maybe this'll help.

884
01:22:59,938 --> 01:23:01,812
"Hi, baby.

885
01:23:01,982 --> 01:23:05,731
The man who gave you this
key is an old friend...

886
01:23:05,903 --> 01:23:08,228
...and a good lawyer.

887
01:23:09,406 --> 01:23:14,649
If you need any help or advice after
you read this, give him a call.

888
01:23:14,828 --> 01:23:18,280
They say that confession
is good for the soul...

889
01:23:18,457 --> 01:23:20,782
...so here goes.

890
01:23:22,920 --> 01:23:27,048
On August 11 th, 1916...

891
01:23:27,841 --> 01:23:31,341
...I was a guest aboard
Alfie Alperirs yacht...

892
01:23:31,512 --> 01:23:35,011
...which was returning from Catalina.

893
01:23:35,807 --> 01:23:40,553
I witnessed Alfie Alperin fighting
with his first wife.

894
01:23:41,688 --> 01:23:45,935
Then he hit her,
and pushed her overboard.

895
01:23:47,152 --> 01:23:49,275
When he saw me...

896
01:23:50,572 --> 01:23:53,242
...I was sure he was going to kill me.

897
01:23:53,408 --> 01:23:55,068
Instead...

898
01:23:55,244 --> 01:23:58,992
...he led me to his cabin,
where he beat me...

899
01:23:59,164 --> 01:24:01,121
...and raped me.

900
01:24:01,291 --> 01:24:04,458
Afterwards, he said that if I kept
my mouth shut...

901
01:24:04,628 --> 01:24:07,582
...he would set me up in business.

902
01:24:09,007 --> 01:24:12,756
Now, baby, I want you to give this...

903
01:24:12,928 --> 01:24:16,546
...give this letter
to the district attorney.

904
01:24:17,266 --> 01:24:19,507
It will protect you."

905
01:24:27,067 --> 01:24:30,234
It's an exciting evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

906
01:24:30,445 --> 01:24:34,823
We expect a gala turnout tonight
of major stars.

907
01:24:34,992 --> 01:24:38,443
Arriving now is Mr. Alfie Alperin.

908
01:24:48,755 --> 01:24:50,878
No statement right now, okay?

909
01:25:17,910 --> 01:25:21,694
The press conference is all set.

910
01:25:22,372 --> 01:25:24,164
Any other news?

911
01:25:34,259 --> 01:25:36,133
What's wrong?

912
01:25:37,721 --> 01:25:40,888
Mix and Wyatt are at the hospital.

913
01:25:41,308 --> 01:25:43,514
Can they hurt you?

914
01:25:48,232 --> 01:25:50,604
I better get dressed.

915
01:26:03,705 --> 01:26:08,663
So silly, losing my balance
and falling over like that.

916
01:26:11,088 --> 01:26:13,080
Is that you, Tom?

917
01:26:13,757 --> 01:26:15,631
Yes, Christina.

918
01:26:18,053 --> 01:26:22,181
I saw Michael. He sends his love.

919
01:26:25,435 --> 01:26:29,848
- He didn't kill that girl, did he?
- No.

920
01:26:30,023 --> 01:26:34,685
No, I'm sure Alfie killed her,
just like I'm sure he did this to you.

921
01:26:34,862 --> 01:26:37,103
Why do you protect him?

922
01:26:41,201 --> 01:26:42,993
Because...

923
01:26:44,204 --> 01:26:46,576
...he's not Michael's father.

924
01:26:46,748 --> 01:26:53,118
He promised me that if I married him,
he'd raise Michael as his own son.

925
01:26:54,423 --> 01:26:57,626
I guess for a while he even tried.

926
01:26:57,801 --> 01:27:01,633
But the thought of another man...

927
01:27:03,182 --> 01:27:08,306
Then, when the doctor
told him that we...

928
01:27:09,104 --> 01:27:13,517
That he couldn't have children...

929
01:27:13,692 --> 01:27:16,313
...he grew to hate Michael.

930
01:27:17,487 --> 01:27:20,773
I did everything I could
to protect him.

931
01:27:22,159 --> 01:27:25,326
What about Michael's real father?

932
01:27:26,455 --> 01:27:28,032
He never knew.

933
01:27:36,173 --> 01:27:40,171
I don't seem to have had much luck
with my men, have I, Wyatt?

934
01:27:45,432 --> 01:27:47,472
I'm so tired.

935
01:27:48,644 --> 01:27:50,636
Try to rest.

936
01:27:52,689 --> 01:27:55,893
He'll never bother you again, my dear.

937
01:28:05,160 --> 01:28:10,403
Welcome to the first annual
Academy Awards.

938
01:28:16,797 --> 01:28:20,841
Before we start handing out
our little statuettes...

939
01:28:21,009 --> 01:28:24,628
...I wanna introduce
an entrepreneur...

940
01:28:24,847 --> 01:28:30,221
...a brilliant clown who retired his
tuxedo coat and baggy pants...

941
01:28:30,435 --> 01:28:34,516
...and is now one of Hollywood's
most successful producers.

942
01:28:34,690 --> 01:28:39,435
Known by millions of his adoring fans
as "The Happy Hobo":

943
01:28:39,611 --> 01:28:42,281
Mr. Alfie Alperin.

944
01:29:03,385 --> 01:29:06,054
- Landmark in Hollywood history.

945
01:29:06,221 --> 01:29:09,388
Arriving now, we can see Tom Mix.

946
01:29:09,558 --> 01:29:13,935
But who's that he's got in the car
with him? It's Wyatt Earp!

947
01:30:33,475 --> 01:30:35,017
Thank you.

948
01:30:39,231 --> 01:30:42,066
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

949
01:30:42,234 --> 01:30:45,021
Thank you for remembering.

950
01:30:48,407 --> 01:30:53,911
Congratulations
to all of us here today...

951
01:30:54,496 --> 01:30:59,538
...for being here to celebrate this
most important event for our industry.

952
01:31:03,172 --> 01:31:05,294
As some of you know...

953
01:31:06,508 --> 01:31:10,838
...my dearest wife, Christina,
is seriously ill in the hospital.

954
01:31:11,013 --> 01:31:17,133
So unfortunately, I'm gonna have to
leave before you honour the winners.

955
01:31:17,311 --> 01:31:21,807
Let me just say this in parting:
Have fun, enjoy yourselves...

956
01:31:21,982 --> 01:31:25,565
...and those who are
working at Alperin, my studio...

957
01:31:25,736 --> 01:31:31,240
... especially the ladies,
don't stay up too late, all right?

958
01:31:31,408 --> 01:31:34,907
Enjoy yourselves. God bless.
Have fun.

959
01:32:06,026 --> 01:32:07,769
Alperin?

960
01:32:09,154 --> 01:32:11,361
I'm taking you in.

961
01:32:11,532 --> 01:32:14,782
How can you do that?
You're not the law here.

962
01:32:14,952 --> 01:32:19,364
No, just a citizen making sure
a murderer doesrt escape.

963
01:32:19,540 --> 01:32:21,449
I'll shoot if I have to.

964
01:32:24,753 --> 01:32:26,461
You're insane.

965
01:32:27,798 --> 01:32:32,792
This is Candace Girard's confession.
She saw you murder your first wife.

966
01:32:34,054 --> 01:32:38,348
You're making a scene, Mr. Earp.
Walk with me to the stairs.

967
01:32:38,517 --> 01:32:40,426
If I don't?

968
01:32:40,602 --> 01:32:44,267
I killed Candy.
I've got nothing to lose.

969
01:32:44,439 --> 01:32:47,109
- Victoria.
- Go on, Alfie.

970
01:32:47,568 --> 01:32:49,607
Get out of here, Alfie.

971
01:32:49,945 --> 01:32:52,151
Walk to the stairs.

972
01:33:02,040 --> 01:33:05,160
You couldn't have beaten
Candace up like that.

973
01:33:05,335 --> 01:33:09,167
You and Dutch find her
after Alfie got through with her?

974
01:33:09,339 --> 01:33:13,966
- Finish her off with an ice pick?
- And I loved every minute of it.

975
01:33:15,012 --> 01:33:18,879
Hold it right there, Earp.
Get your hands up.

976
01:33:19,933 --> 01:33:23,634
Get away from him, Miss Alperin.
Dib, get his gun.

977
01:33:28,400 --> 01:33:33,145
We got a report from Paso Robles.
Four men were killed at Mix's ranch.

978
01:33:33,322 --> 01:33:36,572
- Yep.
- You admit you know about it?

979
01:33:36,742 --> 01:33:40,989
Sure. I killed them. Well, two
of them. Tom got the other two.

980
01:33:43,248 --> 01:33:46,249
- I arrest you for murder.
- Let's go.

981
01:33:46,418 --> 01:33:48,327
Get back!

982
01:33:48,504 --> 01:33:51,255
- What the hell?
- Interesting development.

983
01:33:51,423 --> 01:33:53,546
- Get out of the way.
- He can't.

984
01:33:53,759 --> 01:33:55,218
- What's this?
- Vickie.

985
01:33:55,385 --> 01:33:59,383
- He can hurt Alfie. I won't let him.
- But not like this.

986
01:33:59,556 --> 01:34:02,676
- We'll take care of him.
- She killed Candy.

987
01:34:02,851 --> 01:34:04,891
Alfie has paid you a fortune.

988
01:34:05,062 --> 01:34:08,727
- Just go down the stairs!
- There's too many witnesses.

989
01:34:08,899 --> 01:34:10,773
- Miss Alperin...
- No!

990
01:34:19,618 --> 01:34:23,450
- Victoria!
- No, Dutch. It's gone too far. Go away.

991
01:34:23,997 --> 01:34:26,868
- Oh, Christ.
- You son of a bitch!

992
01:34:29,711 --> 01:34:31,503
No! Dutch!

993
01:34:45,102 --> 01:34:49,396
- Dutch, give me the gun.
- Tom, go get Alfie.

994
01:34:52,067 --> 01:34:53,775
It hurts.

995
01:34:54,444 --> 01:34:56,935
Why did you kill Candy?

996
01:34:58,031 --> 01:35:03,951
She was gonna tell about
what happened on the boat.

997
01:35:04,121 --> 01:35:07,122
I had to protect Alfie.

998
01:35:09,668 --> 01:35:12,752
You don't understand, do you?

999
01:35:14,131 --> 01:35:16,005
Sometimes...

1000
01:35:16,842 --> 01:35:20,092
...bad people like me and Alfie...

1001
01:35:21,263 --> 01:35:24,299
...only have each other.

1002
01:35:26,560 --> 01:35:30,392
Daddy. Daddy...

1003
01:36:05,432 --> 01:36:10,390
Go! Don't slow down for anything.
Get me to the boat as fast as you can.

1004
01:36:10,562 --> 01:36:14,145
- Did you hear about Mrs. Alperin?
- No.

1005
01:36:14,316 --> 01:36:17,352
It was on the radio. She died.

1006
01:36:17,528 --> 01:36:19,022
Just step on it!

1007
01:36:29,081 --> 01:36:31,619
I think we're being followed.

1008
01:36:39,132 --> 01:36:41,802
Come on. Can't you shake him?

1009
01:36:43,720 --> 01:36:47,469
Just get me to the boat quickly.
It's all I ask.

1010
01:36:47,641 --> 01:36:50,310
You stop this goon behind us...

1011
01:36:50,477 --> 01:36:54,605
...or you're gonna see the inside
of Folsom for a long time.

1012
01:36:54,773 --> 01:36:58,142
Do you hear me, Arthur?
Do you hear me?

1013
01:37:32,311 --> 01:37:35,477
Where are you going?
You passed the boat!

1014
01:37:35,814 --> 01:37:39,515
Hey! Son of a bitch! No! No! No!

1015
01:37:39,818 --> 01:37:40,849
No!

1016
01:38:09,473 --> 01:38:11,679
- Help! Help!
- Shit!

1017
01:38:11,975 --> 01:38:14,466
- I can't swim!
- Hang on, Arthur!

1018
01:38:14,770 --> 01:38:16,809
Help! Help!

1019
01:38:29,284 --> 01:38:30,944
Relax!

1020
01:38:43,298 --> 01:38:45,624
- You okay, Mr. Mix?
- I'm all right.

1021
01:38:45,801 --> 01:38:49,633
- What about Mr. Alperin?
- Better call the police.

1022
01:38:49,805 --> 01:38:52,378
Sorry.
You'd have drowned us both.

1023
01:38:52,558 --> 01:38:55,642
Better to drown.
They'll put me away for life!

1024
01:38:55,811 --> 01:38:58,302
- Think you can walk?
- Yeah.

1025
01:38:58,480 --> 01:39:00,224
Then why don't you start?

1026
01:39:00,399 --> 01:39:04,728
Keep walking till you find a place
you want to start a new life.

1027
01:39:04,903 --> 01:39:06,563
You mean it?

1028
01:39:07,948 --> 01:39:12,610
I'm the hero, Arthur.
I always mean what I say.

1029
01:39:12,786 --> 01:39:14,695
Thanks.

1030
01:39:14,872 --> 01:39:18,821
Por nada, amigo. Get going.

1031
01:40:29,279 --> 01:40:31,605
You know something, pardner?

1032
01:40:32,991 --> 01:40:36,775
You're developing a real knack
for upstaging me.

1033
01:41:14,283 --> 01:41:18,779
Some folks would rest
a whole lot easier if you burned this.

1034
01:41:18,954 --> 01:41:22,489
Or I could open up
the Candy Store again.

1035
01:41:22,666 --> 01:41:24,493
That you could.

1036
01:41:26,503 --> 01:41:28,295
Got a match?

1037
01:41:35,470 --> 01:41:37,297
All aboard!

1038
01:41:39,391 --> 01:41:41,182
Come back.

1039
01:41:41,560 --> 01:41:43,351
You never know.

1040
01:41:48,442 --> 01:41:51,478
Now you take care
of that big guy, will you?

1041
01:41:51,653 --> 01:41:54,773
- I'll miss you.
- And I'll miss you.

1042
01:41:59,077 --> 01:42:00,536
Michael.

1043
01:42:00,704 --> 01:42:04,536
I'll tell you like I told your mother
a long time ago.

1044
01:42:04,708 --> 01:42:08,159
If you ever need help,
you know where to find me.

1045
01:42:08,337 --> 01:42:10,045
Yes, sir.

1046
01:42:14,218 --> 01:42:16,009
All aboard!

1047
01:42:24,853 --> 01:42:26,561
So long, pardner.

1048
01:42:27,439 --> 01:42:29,266
Adiós, amigo.

1049
